First Department,

December, 1957

(December 3, 1957) The People of the State of New York, Respondent, v. Clarence Humphrey, Appellant.

Judgment affirmed. Concur — Peck, P. J., Botein and Valente, JJ; Breitel and Rabin, JJ., dissent and vote to reverse and dismiss on ground guilt was not established beyond reasonable doubt.
